libflate
------------------------------------------
Flate is a template library used to deal with html code in CGI applications.
The library includes C and Perl support. All html code is put in an external
file (the template) and printed using the library functions: variables, zones
(parts to be displayed or not) and tables (parts to be displayed 0 to n
times). Using this method you don't need to modify/recompile your application
when modifying html code, printing order doesn't matter in your CGI code, and
your CGI code is much cleaner.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.30-1
  libflate0-2.0.1-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.24.51-4
  cygport-0.16.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.0-1
  libtool-2.4.2-5
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  http://flate.dead-inside.org/

Canonical download:
  http://flate.dead-inside.org/libflate-2.0.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libflate-2.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libflate-2.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libflate-2.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libflate-2.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libflate0-2.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libflate-devel-2.0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libflate)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libflate.README
  /usr/share/doc/libflate/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libflate/README

(libflate0)
  /usr/bin/cygflate-0.dll

(libflate-devel)
  /usr/include/flate.h
  /usr/lib/libflate.dll.a

